   <documentation>
      <row>
         <Docu><![CDATA[= Action name =
PCK.AUTOMIC_SERVICENOW.PUB.ACTION.UPDATE_CHANGE_REQUEST_STATE

= General description =
This action changes the state of a Change Request in ServiceNow.
If user want to add new state value in State field then user can do add it by making an entry to PCK.AUTOMIC_SERVICENOW.PRV.VARA.CHANGE_REQ_STATE_TYPE object.

= API Reference =
https://developer.servicenow.com/dev.do#!/reference/api/orlando/rest/c_TableAPI#r_TableAPI-PUT

= Inputs =
* System Id*   : Provide change request system id to update its state. E.g. d66d9a0b0fbee3002cc2cd8ce1050e52
* State        : The state to be set for the specified Change Request. Required if 'Custom State' is not provided. E.g. New, Pending
* Custom State : The custom state to be set for the specified Change Request. Required if 'State' is not provided. E.g. Deploy, Pre-Deployment

= Failure Conditions 
* If invalid System ID number is provided.
* If neither of the State nor Custom State is provided.
* If both the State and Custom State are provided.
* If connection parameters are not correct.

= Behavior =
(none)

=Return Value=
* &UC4RB_SN_STATE_VAL#     : Value of the State
* &UC4RB_SN_STATE_DIS_VAL# : Display value of the State


= Outputs =
* Return code is 0 in case of success.
* Return code is non-zero in case of failure.

= Rollback =
(none)


= Example =
Updating CR state to Fixed State
* System ID* : cf1747d10fc3ab002cc2cd8ce1050e8d
* State      : New

Updating CR state to Custom State
* System ID*   : cf1747d10fc3ab002cc2cd8ce1050e8d
* Custom State : Pre-Deployment]]></Docu>
      </row>
   </documentation>
   <scripts>
      <row>
         <process><![CDATA[: SET &COUNT# = 0
:IF &UC4RB_SN_CHANGE_REQ_STATE# NE ""
:  SET &COUNT# = &COUNT# + 1
!Publishing state value
:  SET &ATTRIBUTE_VARA#="PCK.AUTOMIC_SERVICENOW.PRV.VARA.CHANGE_REQ_STATE_TYPE"
:  SET &UC4RB_STATE_ATTRIBUTE#="&UC4RB_SN_CHANGE_REQ_STATE#"
:  INC PCK.AUTOMIC_SERVICENOW.PUB.INCLUDE.SET_VARA_VALUE
:  SET &UC4RB_SN_STATE#=&ATTRIBUTE#
:ENDIF

:IF &UC4RB_SN_CUST_STATE# NE ""
:  SET &COUNT# = &COUNT# + 1
:  SET &UC4RB_SN_STATE#=&UC4RB_SN_CUST_STATE#
:  ENDIF

: IF &COUNT# <> 1
:    STOP MSG, 50, "Either State or Custom State should be provided"
: ENDIF

:SET &UC4RB_SN_TABLE_NAME#="change_request"
]]></process>
      </row>
